Bank to CSV User Guide

Installing the Chrome Extension

If you need to install the Chrome Extension on a new computer please reach out to stricoff92@gmail.com.

Updating the Chrome Extension

Periodically the extension may require maintenence. Events that may trigger maintenence requirements:

  • Backend updates to Chase
  • Backend updates to Google Chrome

How to Update

1) Open the GITHUB DESKTOP application. Ensure the current repository is set to "chase-to-csv-extension". Click "fetch origin" to check for updates.

2) If there is an update to download, click "pull origin" to download the update.

3) Open google chrome and navigate to the extensions page (3 dot menu >> More Tools >> Extensions)

4) Find the "Bank to CSV" extension and click the refresh icon.

5) If you are already on chase's website you must refresh the page.

Accessing the Extension Control

Extensions are accessed via the extension toolbar on the top left corner of the Chrome window. The Bank to CSV extension icon is a capital B.

If you don't see the B icon:

Chase.com

To use the extension: login to chase.com, and nagivate to the accounts page (List of sub accounts). If the extension says "Not on Account Page" refresh the page.

Control Panel Overview

Advanced Options

Plug Account ID is the accounting system's account ID that will offset any debit/credit balance created by the bank transactions. Example: an expense account.

CSV Columns specifies the column ordering in the generated CSV file.

Prefix Columns populate prefix columns with static values. This is useful if the accounting system is expecting additional fields.

  • Include 1 prefix column with the value "1" in every row
    [ "1" ]

Transaction Filters specifies which banking transactions should be included or excluded.

  • Exclude transaction where memo contains "onlinetransfer" (space/case insensitive) and either 8759 or 9031
    [{"TYPE":"exclude","AND":["onlinetransfer"],"OR":["8759","9031"]}]

Account Filters specifies which sub accounts should be included or excluded.

  • Include sub accounts that contain the text "smith" (space/case insensitive)
    [{"INCLUDE":["smith"], "EXCLUDE":[]}]

TROUBLESHOOTING

If the web page freezes or a section of the page does not load the extension may freeze. It may be difficult to tell if the page is frozen or just slow. At certain times the extension moves quickly, other times slowly. The health check and scraper logic is injected and runs within chase's website. This means you can easily interrupt and reset health checks and transaction scrapes by refreshing the page.

If the health check or data scrape fails please refresh the page and retry 2-3 times. If the extension continue to fails or freeze reach out for support.
